MongoDB

MongoDB is a NoSQL database where each record is a document comprising of key-value pairs that are similar to JSon(JavaScript object Notation) objects. MongoDB is a flexible and allows its users to create schema, database tables, etc. Documents that are identifiable by a primary key make up the basic unit of MongoDB. Once MongoDB is installed, users can make use of Mongo shell as well. Mongo shell provides a Javascript interface through which the users can interact and carry out operations(e.g.: querying ,updating records,deleting records).

Express

Express is a Node.js framework. Rather than writing the code using Node.js and creating loads of Node modules, Express makes it simpler and easier to write the back-end code. Express helps in designing great web applications and APIs. Express supports many middlewares which makes the code shorter and easier to write.
